<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">103.ECA/8–1448: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-16T15:00:00-04:00">August 16, 1948—3
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1186. Dept appreciative of your 1514, Aug 14 and is wholly in accord with
                        Embs view as expressed in the latter half of third from last para.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>